parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in rainy or snowy conditions.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working or work intermittently
may start working again after a few minutes
wipers may work only when the vehicle is not in motion
wipers may stop working when the vehicle is driven over a bump or uneven pavement
wipers may work only when the switch is wiggled or the column is adjusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to extended stopping distances, skidding, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light stays on
the vehicle momentarily loses brakes before engaging
the brakes make a rubbing noise
the rear brakes lock up
the vehicle continues to move after applying the brakes
extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to fail to stop, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not respond to pressure
the vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to extended stopping distances, skidding, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear brakes make a scratching noise when braking
the rear brakes lock up
the front brakes wear excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Leading to Loss of Vehicle Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden acceleration
hesitation
or stalling
making it difficult to stop or control; the transmission may lock up or jump out of gear; the vehicle may roll backwards on an incline; the throttle may stick
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transmission oil cooler line can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature failure and loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The transmission oil cooler line may separate from the coupler
causing transmission fluid leaks and overheating; the transmission may experience erratic operation or complete failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may roll backwards on an incline when the foot is taken off the brake; the ABS system may not respond appropriately
leading to loss of vehicle control.
